# Hexagonal Backend

## Package layout (per domain: crm, sales, auth…)
```
internal/crm/
  domain/customer.go      # entity + CustomerRepository interface
  application/customer.go # CustomerService use cases
  adapter/http/customer.go
  adapter/postgres/customer.go
```

## Rules
- Application services receive ports via constructor injection.
- Business logic (SLA, stage transition, quotation calc) lives in application/.
- Code generation: use `application/codegen.go` GenerateCode(prefix, withYear).
- Soft delete customers: `is_active = false`.
- Stage changes: always write `opportunity_stage_history`.

## Router wiring
- `internal/router/router.go` only registers adapter/http handlers.
- Do not add new files under deprecated `internal/module/` — migrate to hexagonal (`internal/crm/`, `internal/sales/`).
